Terra-Forge: The Deep Core
GameFi 2.0 Technical Whitepaper & Game Design Document
Document Version: 2.3.3
Ledger Architecture: L1 Native Asset Protocol
Language: English only
Author: Lead Game Economist & Systems Architect

================================================================================
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
================================================================================

GameFi 1.0 failed because reward tokens were treated as play-to-earn salaries.
Players optimized for immediate cash-outs, causing extraction-first behavior,
hyperinflation, liquidity drainage, and economic collapse.

Terra-Forge: The Deep Core introduces a sustainable GameFi 2.0 paradigm:
  - On-chain NMG is separated from in-game industrial assets (Gold, Miners, Ores, Ingots).
  - Irreversible deflationary sinks (deposits, catalyst burns, upgrade burns) remove NMG from circulation.
  - Smelting rewards are paid from a pre-allocated Reward Reserve — never minted beyond the 21M hard cap.
  - Dynamic emission scaling prevents Reserve cliff collapse as the pool depletes over years.
  - Gold shields casual players from crypto volatility; Gold is the F2P win layer.
  - NMG/NEOX trades at a floating market price on neoxa.exchange — no peg, no fixed exchange rate.
  - Everyone winnable: each player class (Active, Capital, LP, Smartnode) has a designed non-zero path.

This game does NOT use NFTs. Guild Miners are in-game database assets only.

================================================================================
1. WORLDVIEW & NARRATIVE: THE OBSIDIAN CRUST
================================================================================

1.1 The Abyssal Descent
-----------------------
Year 2382. Deep space arrays detect Planetary Core 9-C — a cold rogue body with no
atmosphere, composed of compressed tectonic plates around a radioactive core: The
Obsidian Crust. Hyper-pressurized fractures contain super-dense geodes enriched with
NMG (Neox Miner Guild) crystals — sub-space catalysts for near-instant atomic fusing.

1.2 The Mining Guilds
---------------------
The player is a Guild Master operating orbital command ships. They deploy Biotech
Miners and Cyborg MINERs into deep-core stress zones, extract raw ore, protect it
from radiation, and smelt it in orbital foundries. High-purity NMG-Ingots are
redeemed through the Interstellar Merchants Coalition for liquid NMG.

================================================================================
2. DUAL-TOKEN MICROECONOMICS & ASSET TAXONOMY
================================================================================

2.1 Economic Flow
-----------------
  [ neoxa.exchange ]  NMG / NEOX  (floating market price — NOT a peg)
           |
  NMG (L1, 21M cap) --Irreversible Deposit--> Gold (in-game soft currency)
           |                                        |
           |                                        v
           |                                   Guild Miners (in-game DB)
           |                                        |
           |                                        v
           |                                   Raw Ores (in-game DB)
           |                                        |
           |                                   Orbital Forge (NMG catalyst burn)
           |                                   95% burned | 5% recycled to Reserve
           |                                        |
           +<---- Scaled Reward Reserve payout ---- Premium Ingots (in-game DB)

2.2 Asset Taxonomy
------------------
Asset          | Layer        | Rules
---------------|--------------|--------------------------------------------------
NMG            | Neoxa L1     | Hard cap 21,000,000. Burns on forge/upgrade.
               |              | Withdrawals from Reward Reserve + player deposits.
Gold           | Game DB      | Minted on NMG deposit (one-way). Pays wages, rest,
               |              | repairs, hire costs. F2P win layer (rank, trade).
               |              | Never convertible back to NMG.
Guild Miners   | Game DB      | Biotech / Cyborg. Rarity: Common→Legendary.
               |              | NOT on-chain. NOT NFTs. Tradable in-game only.
Raw Ores       | Game DB      | Copper, Iron, Coal, Mithril, Star-Element.
               |              | Used for smelting only — NOT player-tradable.
Premium Ingots | Game DB      | Bronze, Iron, Mithril, Astral. Redeem for NMG
               |              | from Reward Reserve after catalyst burn confirmed.

2.3 NMG Supply Allocation (21,000,000 total — fixed, never increased)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Allocation              | NMG Amount  | %     | Purpose
------------------------|-------------|-------|----------------------------------
Smelting Reward Reserve | 8,400,000   | 40%   | Pays all ingot redemption rewards
Game Treasury (NMG)     | 4,200,000   | 20%   | Ops, community; replenishment source
Liquidity Bootstrap     | 2,100,000   | 10%   | Initial DEX / market making
Development Fund        | 3,150,000   | 15%   | Vested team & development
Community & Ecosystem   | 3,150,000   | 15%   | Grants, events, partnerships
  └ Tutorial Subsidy Pool (sub-account) | 50,000 cap | Free Bronze catalyst for new players

Smelting NEVER mints NMG. Rewards debit the Smelting Reward Reserve with dynamic
emission scaling (see §3.9). When Reserve falls below 5%, rewards pause until
governance replenishes from Game Treasury (max 10% of Treasury per quarter).

Replenishment sources:
  - Governance: Game Treasury → Reserve (max 10% per quarter)
  - Catalyst recycle: 5% of all catalyst burns return to Reserve; 95% burned on-chain

2.4 Wallet & Exchange Interoperability
--------------------------------------
Supported wallets: Bitget, Atomic, Neoxa Core GUI, any Neoxa L1 wallet.
Block confirmation: ~60 seconds. On-chain actions: deposit, burn, withdrawal.

Wallet sign-in (MVP): Browser extension NOT available at launch. Players MUST
authenticate with Neoxa address + signmessage before accessing the portal.
Flow per https://dev.neoxa.net/ :
  1. Server issues nonce message: terra-forge-login:{nonce}
  2. Player signs with Neoxa wallet (Core GUI, SDK, or compatible tool)
  3. Player submits address + signature; backend verifies via
     POST /agents/verify-message on assets.neoxa.net
  4. Session unlocks portal. NMG deposit remains optional for F2P play.

External exchange: neoxa.exchange — NMG/NEOX pair, 1.5% swap fee to LPs.
NMG and NEOX have a floating market price. There is NO fixed peg between them.

External price reference (updated periodically by ops):
  1 NEOX = 0.00008 USDC
  100 USDC = 1,250,000 NEOX

================================================================================
3. CORE GAMEPLAY LOOP & REFINING MATHEMATICS
================================================================================

3.1 New Player Entry
-----------------------------------------------
Players MUST connect a Neoxa wallet (manual address + signature sign-in at MVP;
browser extension coming later) before accessing the portal. See §2.4.

Every new authenticated account receives 500 Starter Gold (one-time, in-game only).
Players rent or buy a Common Biotech Miner, dispatch, mine, and smelt using
3 free Tutorial Catalyst Subsidies (see §3.8). First NMG wallet deposit is optional.
F2P rent path: 50 Gold / 7 days (vs 200 Gold buy).

Gold is the F2P win layer: leaderboard rank, guild standing, miner progression,
and Gold sinks (rent, buy, repair, rest, upgrades). NMG is the withdrawal layer
— not the only win condition.

3.2 NMG → Gold Conversion (Irreversible)
----------------------------------------
  1 NMG deposited on-chain = 250 Gold minted in-game.
  Conversion is one-way. Gold cannot become NMG.

3.3 Mining Speed Equation
-------------------------
Ore extraction rate for miner i (total raw ore units per hour):

  Φ_i = Φ_base × (1 + α × L_tool) × (1 − β × D) × γ_rarity × γ_depth

Parameters:
  Φ_base = 10 units/hour
  L_tool ∈ {1, 2}  (drill level)
  α = 0.15
  D ∈ [0.0, 1.0]   (fatigue; +0.10 per hour mining)
  β = 0.80         (fatigue penalty)
  γ_rarity: Common 1.0 | Rare 1.25 | Epic 1.60 | Legendary 2.20
  γ_depth:  Surface 1.0 | Mid-Fracture 1.3 | Deep Core 1.6

Fatigue at D = 1.0 halts mining until:
  Camp Rest: 50 Gold (resets D to 0)
  Instant Chemical Cooling: 0.5 NMG burned on-chain (resets D to 0)

3.4 Ore Drop Distribution (per total ore unit mined)
----------------------------------------------------
Zone          | Copper | Iron | Coal | Mithril | Star-Element
--------------|--------|------|------|---------|-------------
Surface       | 45%    | 30%  | 25%  | 0%      | 0%
Mid-Fracture  | 30%    | 25%  | 25%  | 15%     | 5%
Deep Core     | 15%    | 20%  | 25%  | 30%     | 10%

3.5 Durability
--------------
  - Durability: 100 points max.
  - Mining consumes 5 durability per hour.
  - At 0 durability, miner cannot dispatch.
  - Repair: 10 Gold per 10 durability restored.

3.6 Guild Shop — Rent vs Buy (No P2P)
--------------------------------------
Every miner is acquired from the Guild Hall shop. There is NO player-to-player
trading, rental marketplace, or ore marketplace.

Each tier offers two modes:

  RENT  — 25% of buy price, 7-day lease, miner removed at expiry
  BUY   — full price, permanent ownership

Rarity    | Class   | Rent (7 days) | Buy (permanent) | Notes
----------|---------|---------------|-----------------|----------------------------------
Common    | Biotech | 50 Gold       | 200 Gold        | Starter tier
Rare      | Biotech | 200 Gold      | 800 Gold        | —
Epic      | Cyborg  | 15 NMG        | 50 NMG*         | *via deposit at 1:250 Gold
Legendary | Cyborg  | 60 NMG        | 200 NMG*        | Limited: 500 buy per server epoch

Rent rules:
  - Lease timer starts on confirmation; miner removed at expiry (ores kept).
  - Rented miners cannot be upgraded (L_tool locked at 1).
  - Repair/rest costs apply during lease (Gold sinks).
  - Max 2 active rented miners per account.
  - No refund on early return.

Buy rules:
  - Permanent roster slot; eligible for drill upgrade (§5.1).
  - Repair/rest as normal.

3.7 Forging & Smelting Recipes
------------------------------
Raw ores cannot be sold for NMG directly. Smelting burns NMG catalyst on-chain
(95% burned, 5% recycled to Reserve), then credits scaled NMG reward from the
Smelting Reward Reserve.

Ingot         | Inputs                              | Catalyst Burn | Base Reward | Base Net
--------------|-------------------------------------|---------------|-------------|----------
Bronze Ingot  | 100 Copper + 50 Coal                | 0.10 NMG      | 1.20        | +1.10
Iron Ingot    | 150 Iron + 80 Coal                  | 0.50 NMG      | 3.50        | +3.00
Mithril Ingot | 80 Mithril + 10 Iron + 100 Coal     | 2.00 NMG      | 15.00       | +13.00
Astral Ingot  | 50 Star-Element + 150 Mithril + 200 Coal | 10.00 NMG | 85.00  | +75.00

Effective_Reward = Base_Reward × Emission_Multiplier (see §3.9)

Flow: validate materials → deduct ores → on-chain catalyst burn (95/5 split) →
credit scaled NMG from Reward Reserve → log event. If burn fails, rollback.

3.8 Tutorial Catalyst Subsidy (F2P Smelting Gate)
------------------------------------------------
New players receive 3 free Bronze catalyst subsidies per account:
  - Covered recipe: Bronze Ingot only (0.10 NMG catalyst each)
  - Player pays 0 NMG; system burns from Tutorial Subsidy Pool (50,000 NMG cap)
  - After 3 subsidized smelts, normal catalyst required (wallet or in-game balance)
  - Expected F2P yield: ~3.6 NMG in-game (3 × 1.20 base, before emission scaling)

This closes the free entry loop without requiring a wallet deposit.

3.9 Dynamic Reserve Emission Scaling
------------------------------------
Effective_Reward = Base_Reward × Emission_Multiplier

Emission_Multiplier = f(Reserve_Remaining / Reserve_Initial):

  Reserve Level (% remaining) | Multiplier | Player Message
  --------------------------|------------|----------------------------------
  100% – 50%                | 1.0×       | Normal operations
  50% – 20%                 | 0.75×      | Industrial output adjusted
  20% – 5%                  | 0.50×      | Reserve conservation mode
  Below 5%                  | 0× (pause) | Awaiting governance replenishment

Reserve_Initial = 8,400,000 NMG. Reserve_Remaining tracked on-chain / in DB.

3.10 NMG Withdrawal
-------------------
Players withdraw earned NMG (from smelting redemptions) to their connected wallet.
Withdrawals debit in-game balance and transfer from Reward Reserve wallet on L1.
  Minimum withdrawal: 1 NMG
  Daily cap per account: 100 NMG (governance tunable)
  New account cooldown: 24 hours before first withdrawal (Sybil protection)

================================================================================
4. GameFi 2.0 REVENUE SHARE FRAMEWORK
================================================================================

4.1 Active Players (Time-Rich, Capital-Poor)
--------------------------------------------
Start with 500 Starter Gold. Profit via smelting (3 subsidized Bronze first),
Gold progression (rent cheap miners to try, buy to keep), and optional NMG deposit.

4.2 Industrial Investors (Capital-Rich, Time-Poor)
---------------------------------------------------
Purchase (or rent to trial) elite Cyborg miners from the Guild Shop. Dispatch to
deeper zones, smelt high-tier ingots, withdraw NMG. No P2P — investors operate
their own miners directly.

4.3 Liquidity Providers & Traders
---------------------------------
Stake NMG/NEOX on neoxa.exchange. Earn 1.5% swap fees. Independent of game mechanics.

4.4 Smartnode Operators
-----------------------
Stake 1,000,000 NEOX collateral (~$80 USDC at reference price). Host game DB,
matchmaking, and anti-cheat. Receive 45% of L1 block rewards. Smartnodes are the
authoritative source of player state; anti-cheat validates all mining and smelting.

4.5 P2P Systems — Removed (v2.3.0)
------------------------------------
Player-to-player ore marketplace and miner rental are permanently removed.
All acquisition goes through the Guild Shop (§3.6): Rent (7-day lease) or Buy
(permanent). Ores are smelting inputs only — not tradable between players.

4.6 Everyone Winnable — Win Matrix
---------------------------------
Everyone can win differently. Each class has a designed non-zero path:

Player Class          | Primary Win              | Crypto Upfront? | Minimum Viable Path
----------------------|--------------------------|-----------------|---------------------
Active (F2P)          | Gold + tutorial NMG      | No              | 500 Gold → rent Common
                      | + progression            |                 | (50G/7d) or buy (200G) →
                      |                          |                 | mine → 3 subsidized Bronze →
                      |                          |                 | ~3.6 NMG
Active (invested)     | Smelting net NMG         | Optional        | Deposit NMG → buy Epic/
                      | + withdraw               |                 | Legendary → deeper zones
Industrial investor   | High-tier smelting NMG   | Yes (50–200 NMG)| Buy Legendary → Deep Core
                      | + withdraw               |                 | → smelt Mithril/Astral
Liquidity Provider    | 1.5% DEX swap fees       | Yes (LP stake)  | Independent of game;
                      |                          |                 | wins from trading volume
Smartnode Operator    | 45% L1 block rewards     | Yes (1M NEOX)   | Infrastructure yield;
                      |                          |                 | secures all player state

================================================================================
5. ANTI-INFLATIONARY TOKEN SINKS & FLOOR PRICING
================================================================================

5.1 Upgrade Cost Function
-------------------------
Upgrade drill from L to L+1:

  Cost = (L)^2 × φ × NMG + (L)^1.5 × θ × Gold

  φ = 1.50   θ = 25.00   Max L = 2

  L=1→2: 1.50 NMG + 25 Gold
  80% of NMG (1.20) → on-chain burn
  20% of NMG (0.30) → Game Treasury (NMG)

5.2 Treasury & Buyback Architecture
-------------------------------------
Two treasury buckets:
  A) Game Treasury (NMG) — receives 20% of upgrade NMG.
     Can replenish Reserve (max 10% per quarter via governance).
  B) Buyback Reserve (NEOX/USDC) — funded by periodic sale of Treasury NMG on DEX
     and direct stablecoin allocations.

5.3 Floor Price (P_floor)
-------------------------
P_floor = weighted average industrial cost of producing 1 NMG net profit through
smelting, expressed in NEOX per NMG:

  P_floor = Σ(recipe_weight × catalyst_NMG / net_NMG) × P_NMG_MA

  P_NMG_MA = 7-day moving average of NMG/NEOX on neoxa.exchange.

Initial bootstrap P_floor = 0.08 NEOX per NMG (subject to recalculation weekly).

5.4 Buyback Formula (dimensionally corrected)
---------------------------------------------
Trigger: P_NMG < P_floor AND R_treasury > 0

  Q_buyback = min( R_treasury / (δ × P_NMG),  Ψ × Circulating_NMG × (P_floor − P_NMG) / P_floor )

Where:
  Q_buyback       = NMG quantity to buy and permanently burn (NMG)
  R_treasury      = Buyback Reserve balance (NEOX)
  P_NMG           = spot NMG price (NEOX per NMG)
  P_floor         = industrial floor (NEOX per NMG)
  δ               = 10 (max 10% of R_treasury spent per 1-hour recovery window)
  Ψ               = 0.05 (buyback intensity — governance tunable)
  Circulating_NMG = estimated NMG in player wallets + Reward Reserve unclaimed

Purchased NMG is permanently burned. Recovery window cooldown: 1 hour.

5.5 Sustainability Guardrails
-----------------------------
Guardrail                  | Value                    | Purpose
---------------------------|--------------------------|----------------------------------
Daily withdraw cap         | 100 NMG / account        | Prevent Reserve drain spikes
Global daily smelt cap     | 10,000 smelts / server   | Rate-limit extraction
Catalyst burn recycle      | 5% → Reserve, 95% burned | Partial sustainability loop
Reserve runway alert       | Ops alert at 20% left    | Trigger governance review
New account withdraw cooldown | 24 hours              | Sybil protection
Treasury → Reserve replenishment | Max 10% / quarter  | Controlled Reserve refill

5.6 Reserve Runway Model
------------------------
Theoretical max Bronze smelts = 8,400,000 / 1.20 = 7,000,000 bronzes (before scaling).

Example scenario:
  1,000 daily active smelters × 3 bronzes/day = 3,000 smelts/day
  → ~6.4 years runway at Bronze-only, before emission scaling extends further.

Higher-tier ingots drain Reserve 7×–68× faster per smelt than Bronze.
Emission scaling (§3.9) and guardrails (§5.5) are mandatory for multi-year sustainability.

Honest expectation: sustainable for years, not infinite, unless recycling and
governance replenishment keep pace with player growth.

================================================================================
6. WEBSITE & GAME INTERFACE
================================================================================

Visual: Web3 game portal — dark-mode sci-fi with industrial steampunk lore.
Base colors: #1A1A24, #FF5500, #0B0B0F. Web3 accents: #00E5FF, #8B5CF6, #FFD700.
Every page MUST include hero banners and character/zone art — text-only UI is NOT
acceptable. See prompts/13-website-game-interface.md § Image Assets.
Language: English only.

Wallet gate (MVP): Portal blocked until Neoxa sign-in (manual address + signmessage
per https://dev.neoxa.net/). Connect modal includes wallet-gate hero image.

Multi-page architecture (NOT one cramped dashboard):
  /command       — Command Center: one miner card per row; no sidebar
  /guild-hall    — Guild Hall: one tier per scroll chapter; centered portrait
  /forge         — Smeltery Forge: tabbed single-recipe view (not 2×2 grid)
  /market        — Market: hero + one CTA card + flow diagram
  /zones         — Zone Atlas: one zone panorama per section

Layout density (mandatory):
  - Max 4 UI groups above the fold per page
  - Content max-width 960px; section gaps ≥ 64px; card padding ≥ 24px
  - Header: one thin row — balances inside Wallet chip dropdown, not inline chips
  - Max 2 visible buttons per card; secondary actions in "More" menu
  - No data tables on main views; progressive disclosure via modals/expand
  - Zone Intel on /zones only — Command Center links out, no sidebar table

Image requirements: hero + portraits/icons on every page (see prompt 13).

Mining zones (Command Center sidebar + Zone Atlas page):
  Surface       | γ 1.0× | 45% Cu, 30% Fe, 25% Coal, 0% Mithril, 0% Star-Element
  Mid-Fracture  | γ 1.3× | unlock: first Bronze forged
  Deep Core     | γ 1.6× | unlock: Epic or Legendary Cyborg on roster

Tutorial spotlight (cross-page): Guild Hall nav → /guild-hall Rent button →
Confirm → /command dispatch → /forge Bronze → optional NMG deposit.

NOT in portal:
  - Single-page layout stacking Command + Guild + Forge + Market
  - P2P systems (removed v2.3.0)
  - In-game swap widget or browser wallet extension (MVP)

Guild Hall UI: spaced showcase cards with large portraits; [ Rent — X / 7 days ]
and [ Buy — Y forever ] per tier. Roster badges on Command Center only.

6.1 Prototype Implementation Notes
----------------------------------
Browser prototypes (e.g., web/game.html) MUST use canonical numbers from
prompts/16-economy-numbers-bible.md. Common prototype errors that inflate NMG:
  - Mining rate in ores/sec instead of ores/hour (Φ_base = 10/hr)
  - Smelting inputs 20× too small (Bronze must be 100 Copper + 50 Coal)
These errors can produce 1,000+ NMG in minutes instead of ~3.6 NMG over ~57 hours.
See prompts/18-game-prototype-economy-calibration.md for audit checklist.

See prompts/13-website-game-interface.md and prompts/14-landing-page.md for UI specs.
See prompts/16-economy-numbers-bible.md for full numeric reference.
See prompts/17-sustainability-everyone-wins.md for sustainability and win-path docs.
See prompts/18-game-prototype-economy-calibration.md for prototype calibration.
See prompts/19-market-external-marketplace-deferred.md for MVP market scope.
See prompts/20-guild-shop-rent-vs-buy-no-p2p.md for rent vs buy spec (no P2P).

